<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8868> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8868" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 727" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1563> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1563" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Imperium prorogued as Proconsul for the siege of Capua (Liv. 25.41.13; 26.1.2, cf. 8-9). He died from wounds either just before (26.16.1), or soon after, the capitulation of the city (Polyb. 8.7.7-10; 9.3.1-4; Liv. 26.5-7, 8.6-9, 12-16, and 33.4; Plut. Comp. Per. et Fab. 2.1; App. Hann. 40; Zon. 9.6; cf. Sil. It. 13.450-464; 17.300-302; Flor. 1.22.43)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1513> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1513" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 25.2.4, and 3.1; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 46f., 119, 446f., cf. Fast. Fer. Lat., Degrassi 148f.; Val. Max. 2.4.7; Frontin. Str. 4.1.44; Fest. 438 L; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod. Both Consuls cooperated in Campania, in the capture of Hanno's camp at Beneventum, and in reducing Capua (Liv. 25.3.3; 25.7-9, 12-15, 18-20, and 22; App. Hann. 37; cf. Sil. It. 12.479-506). Fulvius remained in charge at Capua while Claudius held the elections in Rome (Liv. 25.41.8-13). See below, Pontifices, on Fulvius." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1499> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1499" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 214, note 6. With Marcellus in the siege of Syracuse, and placed in charge of siege operations while Marcellus campaigned in Sicily (Polyb. 8.3-7, cf. 1.7; LIv. 24.27.4 and 6, 29.4, 30.1, 33.2, and 36.6; Plut. Marc. 13, and 14; Zon. 9.4). Returned to Rome to canvass for the consulship (Liv. 24.39.12; see De Sanctis, 3.2.329-334)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1490> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1490" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Probably Propraetor in Sicily. See Legates, and 214, note 6." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1467> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1467" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See above, Promagistrates. Remained with Marcellus in Sicily and attacked Leontini with him (Liv. 24.30-33). On chronology, see De Sanctis 3.2.330f.; CAH 8.64f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1466> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1466" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Polybius, in a passage referring to the period before Marcellus' arrival, terms Ap. Claudius {Gr} (8.3.1). Livy does not name him in the list of prorogued commands in 24.10.3-4, nor does he mention the title. He evidently held command until Marcellus came (24.27.4-6) to take over the command of eastern Sicily (cf. 24.44.4: finibus eis quibus regnum Hieronis fuisset; and above, on the Praetor Lentulus), then apparently served with him and at his orders until he left for Rome late in 213, when he was succeeded by T. Quinctius Crispinus, an appointee of Marcellus (24.39.12; see 213, Legates). I therefore list him first as a Propraetor, then as a Legate under Marcellus. See Münzer, RE, who lists him as a Propraetor, perhaps correctly, since he may have continued as a Propraetor under the general leadership of the Consul and Proconsul Marcellus, like M. Iunius Silanus, a Propraetor sent with the young Proconsul Scipio to Spain (see 210, Promagistrates) or in a position analogous to that of P. Manlius, who was Praetor in Nearer Spain in 195 with the Consul Cato (see 195, Consuls, and Praetors)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1453> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1453" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Termed {Gr} in Polybius (8.3.1), he held command in eastern Sicily at least until the Consul Marcellus arrived (24.27.4-6). See below, Legates, and note 6." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1452> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1452" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Livy mentions him without title, but he may have been a legate of Marcellus. See below, note 6." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1413> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1413" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Went to Sicily with the soldiers from Cannae (Liv. 23.41.4 and 6, and 32.2). His maneuvers against Bomilcar and against Locri were without success (Liv. 23.41.10-12). Attempted to renew the alliance with Syracuse after Hiero's death (Liv. 24.6.4-6; cf. Polyb. 7.2-3)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1412> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1412" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Election Liv. 23.24.4 Provinces Liv. 23.30.18." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1383> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1383" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Chosen a leader by survivors after Cannae (Liv. 22.53.1-4, and 54.5)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1340> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1340" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A very recent ex-Aedile in 216 (Liv. 22.53.2-3)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1339> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1339" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Patricians were Aediles in odd numbered years (Liv. 7.1.6; Mommsen, RF 1.9-102). See Seidel, 21, who suggests that Livy says proxime in 22.53.3 because he has just used the phrase priore anno." .
